DirectX 10 or higher mush use FEATURE_PER_SHADER_INPUT_LAYOUT_CACHE feature, because
ID3D10Device::CreateInputLayout takes compiled shader as input parameter.

In other case we can have strange behaviour. For example:
- Shader A use input structure SVF_P3F_T3F and use only POSITION vector;
- Shader B use input structure SVF_P3F_T3F and use POSITION and TEXCOORD0 vectors;
- If Shader A will invoke first then DirectX may create input layout for SVF_P3F_T3F structure without TEXCOORD0 vector and Shader B will always take zero vector in TEXCOORD0 paramter.
